@{
    ViewBag.Title = "Home Page";
}

<div class="jumbotron">
    <h1>Animal Shelter 101</h1>
    <p class="lead">This website has been created for all Animal Shelters. The purpose is to help employees within an animal shelter and all other animal shelters keep track of all their needs.</p>
</div>

<div class="row">
    <div class="col-md-4">
        <h2>Find an Animal Shelter</h2>
        <p>
            All Animal Shelters present on the list are one's that currently have animals avaliable for adoption. A user can add, remove, or edit a shelter based off of updates they see necessary. You can navigate to this page from the menu at the top of the page.
        </p>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-4">
        <h2>Find an Animal</h2>
        <p>The Avaliable Animals tab allows you to search for all animals avaliable for adoption. This will help employees, volunteers, and even veterinarians search for animals quicker in order to provide feedback to a potential customer. You can navigate to this page from the menu at the top of the page.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-4">
        <h2>Find a Vetrinary Clinic</h2>
        <p>For management personnel that want to see which vets work with which shelters, just navigate to the Vet Clinic tab at the top of the page in order to recieve a list of vet clinics and which shelters they belong to. Management teams can update, add, and delete vet clinics when they see it necessary.</p>
    </div>
</div>